1
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:08,900
I was a bit tense.

2
00:01:10,208 --> 00:01:12,083
Will they let us do it again?

3
00:01:12,375 --> 00:01:15,458
We'll do it as often as we like.

4
00:01:15,750 --> 00:01:18,042
Adrien, finish in the visitor's room
in five minutes.

5
00:01:20,792 --> 00:01:21,625
I love you.

6
00:01:23,417 --> 00:01:26,583
In spite of the aggro
that's brought you?

7
00:01:28,083 --> 00:01:30,125
That'll all soon be over.

8
00:01:32,083 --> 00:01:34,542
Amélie drew this for you.

9
00:01:36,708 --> 00:01:37,958
This how she see's us.

10
00:01:38,542 --> 00:01:40,333
When you get out...

11
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:46,750
So, was it good?

12
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:49,300
The next time we'll make it a 3...

13
00:01:50,375 --> 00:01:51,375
or a 4.

14
00:02:32,958 --> 00:02:34,667
What's the big idea?

15
00:02:34,917 --> 00:02:36,708
You wanna leave here
in a coffin?

16
00:02:38,083 --> 00:02:40,875
So what?
Makes more for you.

17
00:02:41,667 --> 00:02:44,667
You know where
the goddamn cash is.

18
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:47,125
Is it safe?

19
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:49,500
I can put some buddies
on the job.

20
00:02:49,792 --> 00:02:51,917
They'll guard it
'til we get out.

21
00:02:52,375 --> 00:02:54,083
I wouldn't trust
any buddies of yours.

22
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:55,750
Yeah!

23
00:02:57,958 --> 00:03:00,417
And any reason why I
should trust YOU?

24
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:15,583
That's a nice drawing.

25
00:03:15,958 --> 00:03:16,792
Is it your daughter's?

26
00:03:17,083 --> 00:03:19,208
I didn't think
we were on speaking terms.

27
00:03:19,583 --> 00:03:21,792
It was good like that.

28
00:03:22,417 --> 00:03:23,792
You know...

29
00:03:24,417 --> 00:03:26,792
there's not much nice
in the world.

30
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:29,833
You gotta hang on to it.

31
00:03:32,417 --> 00:03:33,500
Come on you two,

32
00:03:33,875 --> 00:03:34,542
out!

33
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:36,958
Time for a walk

34
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:39,792
Why I would go out today?

35
00:03:40,458 --> 00:03:41,542
Nice weather.

36
00:03:41,958 --> 00:03:43,417
You know the risk
I'd be taking.

37
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,792
You didn't have to assault that girl.

38
00:03:47,583 --> 00:03:49,792
I did NOT do it.

39
00:03:50,167 --> 00:03:51,625
Yeah... I was forgetting.

40
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:55,042
And I suppose your stickups
were done by your twin brother.

41
00:03:55,292 --> 00:03:56,708
Or you wanted to pay for

42
00:03:57,083 --> 00:03:58,500
your sick mother's operation.

43
00:03:58,750 --> 00:03:59,750
Can I go now?

44
00:04:04,667 --> 00:04:07,750
OK you scum...
move it!

45
00:04:09,542 --> 00:04:11,333
Everyone here?

46
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:13,208
Let's go!

47
00:04:30,042 --> 00:04:32,417
Isn't your rock-spider pal coming?

48
00:04:32,708 --> 00:04:34,083
Scared, is he?

49
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:39,750
He's saying...

50
00:04:40,167 --> 00:04:43,500
I don't give a fuck
what apes say.

51
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:45,958
Translate that!

52
00:05:25,250 --> 00:05:26,833
I'm innocent.

53
00:05:27,208 --> 00:05:29,667
I know I'll be cleared eventually.

54
00:05:31,042 --> 00:05:33,875
I've got to survive
in this rat-hole.

55
00:05:35,417 --> 00:05:37,792
I'm called a rock-spider.
They want me dead.

56
00:05:39,125 --> 00:05:43,292
I continue praying my ordeal
will come to an end.

57
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:48,542
You sure?

58
00:06:11,875 --> 00:06:12,625
You get out.

59
00:06:13,042 --> 00:06:14,208
Without making trouble.

60
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:17,250
If you don't wanna cop shit...

61
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:18,792
then scram.

62
00:06:31,667 --> 00:06:32,667
Don't you move.

63
00:06:42,167 --> 00:06:42,833
What do you want?

64
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:47,500
As you don't go out,

65
00:06:47,875 --> 00:06:49,583
we've come to pay you a visit.

66
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:58,917
You hear... repeat it.

67
00:06:59,542 --> 00:07:01,583
"Spasiba".

68
00:07:01,958 --> 00:07:03,375
Go on... repeat it.

69
00:07:03,625 --> 00:07:04,625
Spasiba.

70
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,208
That means thank you.
You'll repeat it.

71
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:08,458
Understood?

72
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:18,375
We'll see if the little girls
get you excited now.

73
00:07:35,417 --> 00:07:36,333
That's enough.

74
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,208
Qu'est-ce tu veux?

75
00:07:46,167 --> 00:07:47,625
We better go down
before there's serious shit.

76
00:08:03,292 --> 00:08:05,333
That's enough... stop!

77
00:08:05,708 --> 00:08:07,500
Shut up... get out!

78
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,875
You shouldn't have
got involved.

79
00:08:41,667 --> 00:08:43,000
6 months more.

80
00:08:43,375 --> 00:08:44,875
Because you defended him.

81
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:47,458
That's not what
the report says.

82
00:08:49,583 --> 00:08:52,333
The employment agency's
got nothing for me.

83
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:54,250
I can't afford the nanny.

84
00:08:54,958 --> 00:08:57,667
I can't afford
the speech therapist.

85
00:08:59,375 --> 00:09:00,958
And we've got all that money.

86
00:09:04,625 --> 00:09:07,625
Do you realise that
this guy Franck Adrien,

87
00:09:07,917 --> 00:09:11,083
went into hiding near our place
after his stick-up.

88
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:13,917
In Nièvre.

89
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:17,167
He's been put with me
to protect me.

90
00:09:17,917 --> 00:09:20,042
I'm there to protect you.

91
00:09:20,458 --> 00:09:22,000
That's true.

92
00:09:28,792 --> 00:09:31,500
Why don't you tell me
where you've hidden it?

93
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:33,000
I'd just take what we need.

94
00:09:37,208 --> 00:09:39,000
Trust me for once.

95
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:44,583
The reason I'm here's
because I was trusting.

96
00:09:45,875 --> 00:09:48,250
I don't get to sleep.
Every other day,

97
00:09:48,667 --> 00:09:50,625
they forget my medication.

98
00:09:51,042 --> 00:09:53,708
The lawyer's going to see
what he can do.

99
00:09:54,792 --> 00:09:56,500
You believe I'm going
to get out of this?

100
00:09:56,875 --> 00:09:58,667
Of course.

101
00:09:58,958 --> 00:10:02,542
Her mother said to the judge
that she'd invented everything.

102
00:10:02,958 --> 00:10:05,625
He's going to question her
and she's going to crack.

103
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,125
You're getting out...
it's going to happen.

104
00:10:08,417 --> 00:10:09,958
You'll give me a child.

105
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:16,583
You didn't need to
bring her in here.

106
00:10:16,958 --> 00:10:17,958
This is no place for her.

107
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:19,542
She wanted to come.

108
00:10:20,625 --> 00:10:21,625
What'd she say?

109
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,417
She wanted to see her father.

110
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:25,750
While I'm in here
I'm not her father.

111
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,375
I don't want her to see me
as a convict.

112
00:10:30,542 --> 00:10:32,667
I'm sorry, Franck.

113
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:36,208
We miss you so.

114
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:39,750
I miss both of you, too.

115
00:11:07,167 --> 00:11:08,792
Amélie, you'll fall over.

116
00:11:10,542 --> 00:11:11,208
Careful!

117
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,167
What a cutie!

118
00:11:14,917 --> 00:11:16,958
What's your name?

119
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,625
She can't reply.

120
00:11:21,042 --> 00:11:22,667
She has speaking problems.

121
00:11:23,583 --> 00:11:25,542
She's going to learn to speak.

122
00:11:25,917 --> 00:11:27,625
It'll take time.

123
00:11:30,375 --> 00:11:32,500
She may be right
to take her time.

124
00:11:34,250 --> 00:11:35,333
Say goodbye.

125
00:11:40,792 --> 00:11:43,000
'Bye, Amélie.

126
00:12:12,708 --> 00:12:14,750
You make a move
and you're a vegetable.

127
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:19,125
You wanna kill me, Novick?

128
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:21,417
Don't you wanna get your dough?

129
00:12:21,708 --> 00:12:24,958
Exactly... the Russkie won't miss you.

130
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:27,125
I wanna know
where the cash's stashed.

131
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:33,250
So my buddies
can take care of it.

132
00:12:33,542 --> 00:12:35,667
Look, they're not far away.

133
00:12:41,708 --> 00:12:43,750
You've got nothing to say?

134
00:12:44,042 --> 00:12:45,208
Go fuck yourself.

135
00:12:45,458 --> 00:12:46,375
Cough up!

136
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:52,875
You know Marco's hideout

137
00:12:53,125 --> 00:12:53,875
I'm listening.

138
00:12:54,292 --> 00:12:56,000
It is under the false floor.

139
00:13:53,458 --> 00:13:54,542
G'day, Franck.

140
00:13:57,917 --> 00:13:59,875
How long have I been here?

141
00:14:00,125 --> 00:14:01,292
4 days.

142
00:14:01,542 --> 00:14:03,167
And Novick?

143
00:14:03,917 --> 00:14:05,292
In solitary.

144
00:14:05,542 --> 00:14:07,667
He only got a week.

145
00:14:08,417 --> 00:14:12,542
So he get's out in 3 days...
gotta get outta here quick.

146
00:14:15,208 --> 00:14:18,125
You're worried about your cash?

147
00:14:20,292 --> 00:14:21,375
What are you talking about?

148
00:14:22,042 --> 00:14:23,917
The reason you're in here.

149
00:14:24,292 --> 00:14:26,583
Novick want's to pinch it.

150
00:14:27,042 --> 00:14:28,667
Do you want any help?

151
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:35,167
How?

152
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:37,583
I'm getting out!

153
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:39,917
The girl's retracted her story.

154
00:14:40,292 --> 00:14:42,500
She made it all up from A to Z.

155
00:14:42,792 --> 00:14:45,083
There won't even
be a new trial.

156
00:14:45,792 --> 00:14:50,333
I want to give you
my phone number.

157
00:14:50,583 --> 00:14:51,958
Call when you get out.

158
00:14:52,208 --> 00:14:54,250
This is not a good idea.

159
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:55,917
Why?

160
00:14:56,167 --> 00:14:57,875
I won't forget what you did.

161
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:01,125
Let me help you.
I don't owe you anything.

162
00:15:01,542 --> 00:15:04,167
Yes, that's quite right.

163
00:15:04,417 --> 00:15:05,333
You're right.

164
00:15:07,625 --> 00:15:09,125
OK.

165
00:15:10,083 --> 00:15:11,625
Cheers.

166
00:15:12,958 --> 00:15:14,750
Call me.

167
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,458
There's something you could do.

168
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,083
It's...

169
00:15:21,625 --> 00:15:23,750
call my wife.

170
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:28,125
Tell her I'm well and that
Novick's watching her.

171
00:15:32,042 --> 00:15:33,667
And then also,

172
00:15:33,917 --> 00:15:36,750
she should see my father,
he'll help her.

173
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:47,250
Could you do that for me?

174
00:15:47,667 --> 00:15:50,583
Sure, you can trust me.

175
00:16:34,042 --> 00:16:36,167
Nothing's changed.
We even tidied your cell.

176
00:16:36,458 --> 00:16:37,708
Novick's out?

177
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:42,292
He said you wanted
to take his share.

178
00:16:42,583 --> 00:16:43,750
He wanted to kill you.

179
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:46,958
He's been transferred to Fresnes.
Happy?

180
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:00,333
Cigarettes?
I been waiting 3 days.

181
00:17:08,583 --> 00:17:10,083
Adrien.

182
00:17:10,333 --> 00:17:11,792
Visitors room.

183
00:17:39,083 --> 00:17:40,875
You can feel the evil in here.

184
00:17:41,125 --> 00:17:42,750
The color-scheme
doesn't help.

185
00:17:44,208 --> 00:17:45,833
Nobody made you come.

186
00:17:47,292 --> 00:17:50,958
Manuel Carrega,
constabulary captain.

187
00:17:52,208 --> 00:17:53,667
Has something happened to Anna?

188
00:17:54,042 --> 00:17:55,833
Anna?

189
00:17:57,875 --> 00:18:01,917
I've got questions regarding
Jean-Louis Maurel.

190
00:18:02,292 --> 00:18:03,292
Maurel?

191
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:05,500
He shared your cell.

192
00:18:06,042 --> 00:18:08,417
You know he was accused of raping
a little girl?

193
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,833
Everyone knew about it.
He's been found innocent.

194
00:18:14,083 --> 00:18:17,042
What did he tell you
about his life?

195
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,292
I wasn't interested.

196
00:18:19,542 --> 00:18:22,792
He told me he was from Nièvre,
I've lived there and we talked a bit
about it.

197
00:18:23,208 --> 00:18:25,917
He mention any places, people?

198
00:18:27,042 --> 00:18:28,667
What are you on about?

199
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,333
I'm not on about him...
but I am about his next victims.

200
00:18:33,792 --> 00:18:35,375
Wasn't he the victim?

201
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:38,750
Legally, yes.

202
00:18:40,875 --> 00:18:43,958
Do I trust
what he's capable of?

203
00:18:44,375 --> 00:18:46,667
Didn't the girl
retract her story?

204
00:18:50,292 --> 00:18:54,042
Maurel's wife
managed to get to her.

205
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:56,208
You haven't charged her?

206
00:18:56,833 --> 00:18:58,958
I'm looking for proof.

207
00:18:59,208 --> 00:19:01,750
I need your testimony.

208
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,000
What have you seen

209
00:19:03,375 --> 00:19:05,583
or heard while you
were with him?

210
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:06,958
He seemed quite normal.

211
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:08,542
He's a manipulator.

212
00:19:08,917 --> 00:19:09,667
He's cunning.

213
00:19:10,417 --> 00:19:12,375
He's fooled more than one person.

214
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:15,042
He hasn't fooled me.

215
00:19:15,292 --> 00:19:19,458
20 years ago I came to France
for a woman.

216
00:19:19,708 --> 00:19:21,667
She'd left a guy
who beat her up.

217
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:26,000
I warned that her ex
was dangerous.

218
00:19:26,417 --> 00:19:28,208
For nothing.

219
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:30,875
He set fire to where we lived.

220
00:19:31,167 --> 00:19:33,125
She's dead.

221
00:19:33,375 --> 00:19:35,750
I've survived.

222
00:19:37,417 --> 00:19:41,500
I've escaped death

223
00:19:41,875 --> 00:19:43,250
to help save others.

224
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:53,667
If anything else

225
00:19:54,083 --> 00:19:54,833
comes back to you.

226
00:19:55,083 --> 00:19:56,458
And if you'd just come
from the asylum?

227
00:19:56,833 --> 00:20:01,042
Believe me...
I'm not the mad one.

228
00:20:10,625 --> 00:20:13,625
The answering machine contains
too many messages.

229
00:20:13,875 --> 00:20:17,208
Please try again later.
Goodbye.

230
00:20:25,958 --> 00:20:26,875
Come on.

231
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:51,000
I'm taking you to the meeting.

232
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:54,042
He had to come
Were are you going?

233
00:20:54,417 --> 00:20:55,875
Not far.
He'll pay double.

234
00:21:05,625 --> 00:21:11,000
Cinderella following Big Sister, out.

235
00:21:17,167 --> 00:21:18,792
Waiting for Prince Charming.

236
00:21:19,292 --> 00:21:20,917
We'll follow and join up.

237
00:21:21,292 --> 00:21:23,167
OK

238
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:37,417
Is it far?
It's here.

239
00:21:52,083 --> 00:21:53,875
You want to stay?

240
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:55,792
It's him who says what
he wants.

241
00:21:57,667 --> 00:21:58,750
She's perfect.

242
00:21:59,125 --> 00:22:00,667
You can leave us.

243
00:22:12,750 --> 00:22:13,833
Will I move?

244
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:15,792
We don't know if it's him.

245
00:22:18,125 --> 00:22:19,208
What's she doing?

246
00:22:19,583 --> 00:22:21,167
She's confirming.

247
00:22:21,833 --> 00:22:22,917
Let me do it.

248
00:22:23,583 --> 00:22:24,958
You start undressing first.

249
00:22:34,625 --> 00:22:35,708
Your turn.

250
00:22:43,042 --> 00:22:43,792
I'm thirsty.

251
00:22:44,167 --> 00:22:46,208
Could I get a glass of water?

252
00:22:46,458 --> 00:22:47,625
It's Costa, go!

253
00:22:49,250 --> 00:22:51,292
We've got him, boys!

254
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:05,125
Don't move!
Go, go!

255
00:24:06,208 --> 00:24:08,833
Turn over, you fuck!

256
00:24:09,875 --> 00:24:12,417
I wanna see your hands!

257
00:24:14,333 --> 00:24:16,542
Move it!

258
00:24:17,542 --> 00:24:19,167
Move it!

259
00:24:21,958 --> 00:24:24,958
All OK?
He's in the bag.

260
00:24:28,833 --> 00:24:30,542
The Corsican was right.

261
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:33,042
You were perfect.

262
00:25:21,917 --> 00:25:24,667
Come on, get a move on.

263
00:25:24,917 --> 00:25:26,000
You stay there.

264
00:25:27,667 --> 00:25:28,583
Nico,

265
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:30,167
a bit of privacy.

266
00:26:13,167 --> 00:26:14,875
I'm not translating.

267
00:26:56,250 --> 00:26:57,083
Vous êtes 3!

268
00:27:43,792 --> 00:27:45,292
Franck.

269
00:27:46,333 --> 00:27:47,750
I can fix everything.

270
00:28:00,708 --> 00:28:01,542
Nico!

271
00:28:01,917 --> 00:28:03,792
Let me out!

272
00:28:04,167 --> 00:28:05,167
They're going to kill me!

273
00:28:05,583 --> 00:28:07,708
Let me out!

274
00:28:09,500 --> 00:28:12,250
Nico, open the door!

275
00:28:12,875 --> 00:28:14,833
I'll kill you, you fucker!

276
00:28:15,208 --> 00:28:17,250
Nico!
Shit.

277
00:28:19,125 --> 00:28:20,667
Ça va, chef?

278
00:29:45,250 --> 00:29:46,333
2 more.

279
00:29:46,708 --> 00:29:49,000
The Costas will spend Christmas
in the clink.

280
00:29:49,250 --> 00:29:50,000
Hang on...

281
00:29:50,417 --> 00:29:52,375
René is more cunning.

282
00:29:52,750 --> 00:29:54,625
We'll need to be more cunning
to catch him..

283
00:29:55,042 --> 00:29:55,708
Exactly.

284
00:29:59,250 --> 00:30:01,792
Has The Holy Ghost
finished with your cover?

285
00:30:02,625 --> 00:30:04,667
He wants Claire downstairs.

286
00:30:04,958 --> 00:30:07,000
And what do you want?

287
00:30:07,417 --> 00:30:09,125
Couldn't ask for more.

288
00:30:09,500 --> 00:30:10,500
The prisoner

289
00:30:10,875 --> 00:30:12,917
who got out dressed as a guard.

290
00:30:13,917 --> 00:30:16,708
Franck Adrien, in for the bank

291
00:30:16,958 --> 00:30:17,792
stickup.

292
00:30:18,167 --> 00:30:19,500
I know.

293
00:30:19,875 --> 00:30:20,625
So?

294
00:30:21,208 --> 00:30:24,292
He had 2 months to go.
He's not ready.

295
00:30:24,583 --> 00:30:27,417
He's going to make
the usual mistakes

296
00:30:27,792 --> 00:30:29,375
getting back the hidden loot.

297
00:30:30,042 --> 00:30:33,208
Anyone can catch him.
I'm staying on the Costas.

298
00:30:33,625 --> 00:30:35,208
The boss wants the best.

299
00:30:35,458 --> 00:30:38,250
The troop that's just had
3 major convictions...

300
00:30:38,625 --> 00:30:40,208
you and your team.

301
00:30:40,458 --> 00:30:41,542
If it's so simple,

302
00:30:41,917 --> 00:30:43,875
you'll be back with the Costas
in no time.

303
00:31:00,292 --> 00:31:01,375
Thank you, monsieur.

304
00:31:01,750 --> 00:31:03,875
That's OK.

305
00:31:05,667 --> 00:31:08,375
Would you know
where to find the eggs?

306
00:31:08,750 --> 00:31:10,792
They're at the end, through there.

307
00:31:11,958 --> 00:31:14,625
Would it be too much to ask
to come with me?

308
00:31:14,875 --> 00:31:19,000
I always get lost
with all these aisles.

309
00:31:19,792 --> 00:31:21,833
- Yes, follow me.
- Melissa!

310
00:31:23,208 --> 00:31:24,375
I'm waiting for you.

311
00:31:25,042 --> 00:31:26,208
Sorry, gotta go.

312
00:31:26,583 --> 00:31:30,083
Doesn't matter,
I'll find them myself.

313
00:31:42,250 --> 00:31:45,833
The man thwarted the security checks.

314
00:31:46,250 --> 00:31:48,708
Franck Adrien, convicted
for the holdup of the Savings Bank

315
00:31:49,125 --> 00:31:52,375
didn't have more than 8 months
of prison left.

316
00:31:52,750 --> 00:31:56,500
He may be armed and
is considered dangerous.

317
00:32:00,458 --> 00:32:03,250
Got it...
au revoir, monsieur.

318
00:32:16,208 --> 00:32:17,917
Do you think he'll understand?

319
00:32:18,500 --> 00:32:20,958
Nothing to worry about.
The police have good info, now.

320
00:32:23,875 --> 00:32:24,875
Christine,

321
00:32:25,292 --> 00:32:27,750
we knew he'd get out one day.

322
00:32:29,208 --> 00:32:30,125
I've got everything worked out.

323
00:32:31,083 --> 00:32:34,167
He doesn't know what's waiting for him.
Trust me.

324
00:32:34,833 --> 00:32:36,875
Nobody's going to take our
happiness away.

325
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:42,042
She's sleeping?

326
00:32:42,292 --> 00:32:44,667
She looks so adorable
like that.

327
00:32:45,458 --> 00:32:47,667
Thanks for giving her to me.

328
00:32:48,083 --> 00:32:49,958
He's got very few connections.

329
00:32:50,250 --> 00:32:52,458
He avoids his relations.

330
00:32:52,958 --> 00:32:54,042
His wife?
Yeah.

331
00:32:54,458 --> 00:32:57,167
Anna Martens.
She used to visit him.

332
00:32:57,542 --> 00:32:59,583
She's unemployed,
takes care of the kid.

333
00:32:59,833 --> 00:33:01,458
The address she gave

334
00:33:01,875 --> 00:33:03,208
is phony.

335
00:33:03,458 --> 00:33:04,958
And his accomplices?

336
00:33:05,542 --> 00:33:07,333
Guests of the state.

337
00:33:07,583 --> 00:33:09,708
Jérôme Novick
was at Mérancourt.

338
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,167
It wasn't a great love affair.

339
00:33:11,583 --> 00:33:13,958
He attacked Adrien
with a screwdriver.

340
00:33:14,208 --> 00:33:15,125
Nice boy.

341
00:33:15,500 --> 00:33:16,833
I'm going to question him.

342
00:33:17,708 --> 00:33:18,958
How much did they get?

343
00:33:19,375 --> 00:33:20,208
2 million.

344
00:33:20,625 --> 00:33:21,375
2 million!

345
00:33:21,750 --> 00:33:24,292
We've only got back pocket money.

346
00:33:25,292 --> 00:33:27,833
He's going to want
to get the money back.

347
00:33:28,250 --> 00:33:30,625
Watch the places he knows.

348
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:31,750
Houses, bars.

349
00:33:32,042 --> 00:33:34,250
His picture's everywhere.

350
00:33:34,667 --> 00:33:36,875
I've asked for
his visiting room videos.

351
00:33:38,417 --> 00:33:39,500
Ça, c'est quoi?

352
00:33:39,875 --> 00:33:42,542
Those who could've seen him
in their area.

353
00:33:43,167 --> 00:33:43,917
100 calls.

354
00:33:44,167 --> 00:33:46,708
Dobbing-in's a national sport.

355
00:33:47,792 --> 00:33:49,583
Has the media spoken to Anna?

356
00:33:50,542 --> 00:33:51,375
No.

357
00:33:52,833 --> 00:33:56,083
We got an address for Anna
in the suburbs.

358
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:16,500
Who's he?

359
00:34:41,833 --> 00:34:43,333
Anna?

360
00:35:11,500 --> 00:35:13,958
Hey, watch where you're going!

361
00:35:14,250 --> 00:35:17,125
What's going on?

362
00:35:17,500 --> 00:35:18,583
Turn them out!

363
00:35:32,875 --> 00:35:34,292
Nobody leaves.

364
00:35:34,708 --> 00:35:35,792
Are you staying here?

365
00:35:36,167 --> 00:35:37,708
No, I'm covering you.

366
00:36:00,250 --> 00:36:01,833
Police, step aside.

367
00:36:04,625 --> 00:36:05,625
Out of the way!

368
00:36:05,875 --> 00:36:07,500
That's it.

369
00:36:10,250 --> 00:36:12,208
Police, open up!

370
00:36:36,500 --> 00:36:38,042
No one!

371
00:36:40,292 --> 00:36:40,958
Come here.

372
00:36:44,958 --> 00:36:46,417
Look.

373
00:36:49,250 --> 00:36:50,333
We just missed him.

374
00:37:04,500 --> 00:37:06,292
Marco!
Coming!

375
00:37:13,667 --> 00:37:14,417
He's not far away.

376
00:37:14,667 --> 00:37:17,625
We need reinforcements,
He's in the area.

377
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:20,375
With luck, we'll be back
in an hour.

378
00:37:20,750 --> 00:37:23,583
Avec de la chance, dans une heure,
on est rentrés.

379
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:55,250
Don't move!

380
00:37:55,667 --> 00:37:56,667
Don't you move.

381
00:37:58,667 --> 00:37:59,833
Let me past.

382
00:38:00,500 --> 00:38:02,125
Of course!
Anything else?

383
00:38:03,125 --> 00:38:06,083
I can't go back to prison now.

384
00:38:08,333 --> 00:38:09,417
Don't move!

385
00:38:11,875 --> 00:38:12,625
I've learned something

386
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:14,083
very important.

387
00:38:14,542 --> 00:38:16,917
You can't shoot,
I'm not threatening you

388
00:38:17,167 --> 00:38:20,042
You can see I'm unarmed

389
00:38:34,167 --> 00:38:36,375
Adrien is on the street.
Warn everyone!

390
00:38:41,542 --> 00:38:43,083
There he is!
Stop him!

391
00:41:32,250 --> 00:41:33,333
You OK?

392
00:41:33,625 --> 00:41:35,917
Close the next station!

393
00:41:36,292 --> 00:41:39,208
If the train stops
he'll get off.

394
00:42:16,750 --> 00:42:18,292
Is he crazy?

395
00:42:51,250 --> 00:42:54,167
Divide up the zone
and set up road blocks.

396
00:42:56,042 --> 00:42:58,667
I know,
good... thanks.

397
00:42:58,917 --> 00:43:01,458
He's probably already far away.
Here...

398
00:43:01,917 --> 00:43:03,250
yours?

399
00:43:06,667 --> 00:43:07,500
He's crazy.

400
00:43:07,875 --> 00:43:11,375
Something's driving him.
Something really strong.

401
00:43:14,875 --> 00:43:17,542
"Anna, wherever you are,
I'll find you."

402
00:43:17,917 --> 00:43:19,708
She's cleared off
with the cash.

403
00:43:20,750 --> 00:43:21,917
Two for the price of one?

404
00:43:22,333 --> 00:43:25,917
Yeah, that'll make
The Holy Ghost happy.

405
00:46:03,417 --> 00:46:04,417
Yes?

406
00:46:06,375 --> 00:46:08,083
Why did you do it?

407
00:46:08,625 --> 00:46:11,458
Franck, I knew you'd call.

408
00:46:11,708 --> 00:46:12,542
How are you?

409
00:46:13,292 --> 00:46:16,125
Tell me, why did you do it?

410
00:46:19,125 --> 00:46:21,083
Why did you kill her?

411
00:46:21,375 --> 00:46:23,167
It was all her fault.

412
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:28,125
Thank God...
I know how to read people.

413
00:46:28,375 --> 00:46:30,833
Your wife was unreliable.

414
00:46:31,292 --> 00:46:33,958
She would have
given you problems.

415
00:46:36,500 --> 00:46:39,250
I chose to save you
from all that.

416
00:46:40,000 --> 00:46:42,125
What have you done with Amélie?

417
00:46:42,375 --> 00:46:46,292
What have you done with
my little daughter?

418
00:46:46,750 --> 00:46:48,292
Where is she, Maurel?

419
00:46:48,833 --> 00:46:50,333
Have you killed her?

420
00:46:50,583 --> 00:46:54,167
She's a lovely little thing.
I love her very much.

421
00:46:54,417 --> 00:46:56,292
I shan't do her
any harm at all.

422
00:46:56,583 --> 00:46:59,667
Unless you try to find me.

423
00:47:38,583 --> 00:47:39,417
What is it?

424
00:47:39,792 --> 00:47:42,083
He wants us to grab Adrien
on his return.

425
00:47:42,375 --> 00:47:43,458
He's in Corsica.

426
00:47:43,833 --> 00:47:45,417
I'd love to go down to Corsica.

427
00:47:45,792 --> 00:47:46,875
Anna's scrap of paper?

428
00:47:47,250 --> 00:47:48,708
Amélie's drawings.

429
00:47:48,958 --> 00:47:51,250
Naïve style endowed with
a certain potential.

430
00:47:52,833 --> 00:47:54,083
Letters for her guy

431
00:47:54,500 --> 00:47:55,750
that she hadn't sent.

432
00:47:56,167 --> 00:47:57,958
Love letters.

433
00:47:58,708 --> 00:48:02,375
"I understand your gesture.
It's a proof of love."

434
00:48:02,792 --> 00:48:03,625
The stickup.

435
00:48:04,042 --> 00:48:07,208
Why hadn't she posted
this deathless prose?

436
00:48:07,917 --> 00:48:09,958
To be read in prison?

437
00:48:10,375 --> 00:48:11,042
Not on.

438
00:48:11,417 --> 00:48:12,083
They aren't the words

439
00:48:12,458 --> 00:48:16,292
of a woman stabbing
someone in the back.

440
00:48:16,708 --> 00:48:17,375
And Novick?

441
00:48:17,667 --> 00:48:19,792
A heap of new insults.

442
00:48:20,208 --> 00:48:22,667
It's a put-up job between
Adrien and his chick.

443
00:48:23,042 --> 00:48:26,208
We know the addresses
he's given,

444
00:48:26,583 --> 00:48:27,333
except for this one.

445
00:48:29,625 --> 00:48:30,458
Le Pré-sur-Lamure?

446
00:48:30,875 --> 00:48:32,667
What's that?
Their hide-out

447
00:48:33,083 --> 00:48:34,333
after the bank job.

448
00:48:49,500 --> 00:48:51,875
Martin, go round!

449
00:49:03,833 --> 00:49:06,125
What's this?

450
00:49:12,208 --> 00:49:13,667
What's this bullshit?

451
00:49:33,292 --> 00:49:34,208
No thanks.

452
00:50:03,292 --> 00:50:06,542
Are your reinforcements coming?
They're coming.

453
00:50:06,917 --> 00:50:08,417
The policeman's refrain.

454
00:50:08,792 --> 00:50:09,958
Are we gonna find the loot?

455
00:50:10,250 --> 00:50:11,333
If it's not already gone.

456
00:50:13,625 --> 00:50:15,208
What's that?

457
00:50:19,042 --> 00:50:20,833
Why have you come?

458
00:50:21,083 --> 00:50:24,167
It's nothing to do with your daughter.
What would you know?

459
00:50:24,583 --> 00:50:26,000
Best you go home.

460
00:50:27,500 --> 00:50:28,833
We should be Corsican.

461
00:50:29,208 --> 00:50:30,542
There's something here!

462
00:50:32,833 --> 00:50:35,375
Captain, come here.
Stay there.

463
00:50:42,792 --> 00:50:43,875
Look.

464
00:50:50,375 --> 00:50:52,000
Robert, no!
Pull him back!

465
00:50:55,833 --> 00:50:57,958
Nobody touch anything.

466
00:51:12,958 --> 00:51:15,333
It was his daughter?
Yeah. Julie.

467
00:51:15,708 --> 00:51:18,458
Disappeared. He'd been hoping
she was just a runaway.

468
00:51:22,958 --> 00:51:25,500
The guy who did that
is a monster.

469
00:51:28,708 --> 00:51:31,000
Is it one of Adrien's victims?

470
00:51:31,292 --> 00:51:33,833
No way that it fits Adrien's profile.

471
00:51:34,083 --> 00:51:37,083
He has a wife
and a disabled child.

472
00:51:37,458 --> 00:51:38,917
That doesn't fit with a killer

473
00:51:39,167 --> 00:51:41,458
There are always exceptions.

474
00:51:42,708 --> 00:51:44,417
There are some connections.

475
00:51:44,708 --> 00:51:47,500
He was living in the area when
Julie disappeared.

476
00:51:47,750 --> 00:51:51,083
We found his DNA
on the map and the jacket.

477
00:51:51,625 --> 00:51:53,833
That's not all.
What else?

478
00:51:54,333 --> 00:51:57,667
There are 2 other maps
of areas way up in the mountains.

479
00:51:58,000 --> 00:51:59,875
Maybe we'll find other bodies.

480
00:52:00,250 --> 00:52:02,042
We're not going to get
carried away

481
00:52:02,292 --> 00:52:05,083
If it's a serial killer,
they'll want to bring in the Feds.

482
00:52:05,333 --> 00:52:06,917
They'd want the file.

483
00:52:07,292 --> 00:52:09,167
We have to get him now.

484
00:52:09,542 --> 00:52:10,958
Listen, Claire.

485
00:52:11,208 --> 00:52:13,833
They don't teach this
at police school,

486
00:52:14,083 --> 00:52:17,500
but next time, this guy
doesn't get to get away.

487
00:52:18,333 --> 00:52:19,833
Understood?

488
00:52:20,083 --> 00:52:21,250
Quite understood.

489
00:52:21,542 --> 00:52:23,250
Have a good day.

490
00:52:48,417 --> 00:52:49,750
I don't want to hurt you.

491
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,958
What the fuck
are you doing here?

492
00:52:52,250 --> 00:52:54,708
You're going to help me
find Maurel.

493
00:52:55,458 --> 00:52:57,417
Where are your guns?

494
00:52:57,708 --> 00:52:58,958
I don't have any.

495
00:52:59,208 --> 00:53:02,208
Don't take me for an idiot,
where are they?

496
00:53:02,833 --> 00:53:04,458
They're there.

497
00:53:04,708 --> 00:53:06,750
In the cupboard.

498
00:53:14,292 --> 00:53:15,458
Go.

499
00:53:17,125 --> 00:53:19,583
He always lived in the area.

500
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:23,000
I met him 5 years ago.

501
00:53:23,292 --> 00:53:27,542
I questioned him about
a girl from Dijon.

502
00:53:36,167 --> 00:53:37,417
Sylvie Desmée.

503
00:53:37,792 --> 00:53:40,167
He'd been seen talking to her.

504
00:53:40,542 --> 00:53:42,083
I smelled a rat.

505
00:53:42,333 --> 00:53:44,875
Maurel raised
too many questions.

506
00:53:45,375 --> 00:53:47,750
He lied about details.

507
00:53:48,167 --> 00:53:51,500
I sensed that he was
playing with me.

508
00:53:51,792 --> 00:53:53,417
He was a bad one.

509
00:53:55,625 --> 00:53:59,042
The girl was never found...
no body, no proof.

510
00:53:59,292 --> 00:54:02,542
There were the other
disappearances.

511
00:54:10,292 --> 00:54:12,167
The resemblance is striking.

512
00:54:12,542 --> 00:54:14,042
It's been admitted
that it was a serial killer.

513
00:54:14,417 --> 00:54:18,708
But a cop investigates facts,
not potential suspects.

514
00:54:19,125 --> 00:54:20,833
You've gone ahead anyway?

515
00:54:21,500 --> 00:54:24,583
Quietly. Got nowhere for a long time.

516
00:54:24,833 --> 00:54:26,542
He was invisible.

517
00:54:26,792 --> 00:54:31,167
No record, town hall official,
liked by all.

518
00:54:31,542 --> 00:54:34,083
He was never far away
when the disappearances occurred.

519
00:54:34,667 --> 00:54:35,583
Finally,

520
00:54:36,000 --> 00:54:38,708
2 bodies were found
a month apart.

521
00:54:39,083 --> 00:54:41,375
I brought Maurel in,

522
00:54:41,625 --> 00:54:44,792
but his DNA didn't match.

523
00:54:45,042 --> 00:54:46,208
For the second time,

524
00:54:46,625 --> 00:54:47,958
he trapped us.

525
00:54:48,333 --> 00:54:52,250
His sperm sample was at the station,

526
00:54:52,625 --> 00:54:55,875
Next day it'd disappeared.
I was suspected.

527
00:54:57,000 --> 00:54:58,167
At the same time,

528
00:54:58,583 --> 00:55:01,292
he brought a complaint against me
for harassment.

529
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:03,500
I was dismissed.

530
00:55:03,875 --> 00:55:06,333
I'm not allowed
to live near him.

531
00:55:06,625 --> 00:55:07,708
You're no longer
in the constabulary?

532
00:55:08,792 --> 00:55:11,583
No, I lied to you.

533
00:55:11,833 --> 00:55:13,458
I investigate privately.

534
00:55:13,875 --> 00:55:17,125
Bugger! I was hoping
you'd be able to help me.

535
00:55:18,500 --> 00:55:19,875
The little girl's 5.

536
00:55:20,125 --> 00:55:22,167
She doesn't look like these girls...

537
00:55:22,458 --> 00:55:23,708
Could he harm her?

538
00:55:25,083 --> 00:55:26,708
She's not his normal victim type.

539
00:55:26,958 --> 00:55:30,458
If he wanted to have a good time,
he wouldn't hesitate.

540
00:55:31,500 --> 00:55:32,583
I've got the phone number.

541
00:55:33,000 --> 00:55:34,083
An old constabulary captain's

542
00:55:34,500 --> 00:55:35,833
maybe got some contacts?

543
00:55:43,708 --> 00:55:44,792
Want a snort?

544
00:55:45,708 --> 00:55:47,083
- Thanks!

545
00:55:50,917 --> 00:55:52,708
It's good stuff.

546
00:55:57,208 --> 00:55:58,125
The paper?

547
00:56:01,417 --> 00:56:02,958
You know him?

548
00:56:03,208 --> 00:56:04,125
The constabulary have

549
00:56:04,500 --> 00:56:06,792
found 2 more bodies.

550
00:56:07,083 --> 00:56:11,458
